display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu ]]></fr:tex> and column <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\nu ]]></fr:tex>, but 0 otherwise.</fr:p><fr:p>We define the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Elementary Row Matrices</html:dfn> to be one of the following:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>Adding a multiple of one row to another: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {I}+r\mathbf {E}_{\mu ,\nu }]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1\leq \mu \leq  n]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1\leq \nu \leq  n]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu \neq \nu ]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Swapping two rows: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {I}+\mathbf {E}_{\mu ,\nu }+\mathbf {E}_{\nu ,\mu }-\mathbf {E}_{\mu ,\mu }-\mathbf {E}_{\nu ,\nu }]]></fr:tex> which swaps rows <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\nu ]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Multiplying a row by a nonzero constant: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {I}+r\mathbf {E}_{\mu ,\mu }]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1+r\neq 0]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
